1. OWNERSHIP
The "Crowd OS" system architecture, specifically the logic of linking "Stationary Thermal Omni-Nodes" to "Mesh-Networked Wristbands," is the intellectual property of Prasurjya Deka.

2. RESTRICTED USE (NON-COMMERCIAL)
*   No Commercial Use: You may NOT use, copy, modify, or distribute this architecture for any commercial product, military application, or crowd management service without express written permission from Prasurjya Deka.
*   Academic Use: Researchers may reference this work for academic study provided clear credit is given to the creator.

3. LEGAL DISTINCTION FROM PRIOR ART (US PATENT 12392583B2)
This work is legally distinct from the "Body safety device with visual sensing" described in US Patent 12392583B2 (Assignee: GovernmentGPT Inc.).
*   Crowd OS utilizes INFRASTRUCTURE-BASED sensors (clamped to poles/walls) to detect crowd density physics.
*   Crowd OS does NOT utilize body-worn visual sensors or sensors integrated into tactical gear.
*   Any attempt to conflate this stationary infrastructure system with body-worn tactical patents is rejected.

4. THIRD-PARTY ATTRIBUTION
This project utilizes hardware architecture adapted from the open-source "PhysioKit" [Joshi et al., 2023], licensed under CC BY 4.0.
